Durban - An elderly woman is recovering in hospital after she jumped off a bridge on the N2 near Amanzimtoti in KwaZulu Natal on Wednesday morning. According to ER 24 spokesperson Russel Meiring the woman, believed to be in her 60s, sustained moderate injuries after she jumped off the Adams Road bridge. He said ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene at around 7:25 am to find the elderly woman lying in the centre median next to the Armco barriers. "Paramedics assessed the woman and found that she had sustained only moderate injuries and was in a stable condition," said Meiring. He added that the woman was treated and thereafter transported to a nearby provincial hospital for further care. He said SAPS were on scene for further investigations. A year ago a Chatsworth woman jumped to her death of the Umgeni Road interchange onto the N2 south bound highway. Daily News